[SN]TITLE[SN]
Nice 2-2 Caen

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Nice came from two goals down to draw with Caen as they missed the chance to draw level on points with Ligue 1 leaders Monaco.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Ivan Santini headed the visitors in front before Yann Karamoh doubled their lead on 50 minutes.
Mario Balotelli halved the deficit on 71 minutes with his 10th league goal of the season, before Anastasios Donis equalised six minutes later.
Nice move to second on 63 points, a point ahead of Paris St-Germain.
PSG play Lorient on Sunday while Monaco, who lead with 65 points, host Bordeaux on Saturday.
Elsewhere former Newcastle winger Florian Thauvin scored twice as Marseille beats Angers 3-0.
